Course Objective

To enhance students listening and speaking competence by:

(1) appreciating and attending to some essential features of the listening process;
(2) appreciating and attending to some essential features of spoken English;
(3) identifying and employing appropriate strategies for effective communication;
(4) engaging in simulated/authentic language learning/language use situations;
(5) evaluating for themselves their listening and speaking processes.

Performance Objectives

By the end of the course, students should be able to listen and respond effectively by:

(1) processing the linguistic forms;
(2) identifying the intention of the speaker(s);
(3) understanding the whole message rather than individual utterances;
(4) interpreting and evaluating the message conveyed;
(5) responding appropriately in various settings.

By the end of the course, students should be able to listen and respond effectively by:

