2. identifying the intention of the writer and the speaker;
3. understanding messages received and be able to respond appropriately;
4. developing reading aloud skills which are used in classroom presentation;
5. preparing and delivering an oral presentation and managing the subsequent discussion;
6. participating in group / panel discussions;
7. reflecting on learning progress and identifying areas for further development.

